---
description: Safely complete unfinished functionality in existing UI
globs: ["**/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx}"]
alwaysApply: true
---

This app may contain already-designed screens with partially connected functionality.

Rules:
- complete unfinished functionality only where the intended behavior is strongly implied by the existing UI
- wire buttons, tabs, cards, actions, and forms to the appropriate existing logic or route
- if a route is missing, create the smallest safe route required
- if a form submit is missing, connect it safely to the existing intended flow
- if a modal open/close action is missing, connect it without changing UI
- preserve current visuals exactly

Strictly forbidden:
- do not redesign incomplete screens
- do not rewrite flows unless necessary
- do not invent a different UX
- do not add large new feature scope beyond what the current UI already implies
- do not hide broken buttons instead of fixing them

Default behavior:
complete functionality behind the existing UI, not around it.
